  "text": "where x(n) is the output from the matched filter. To obtain accurate autocorrelation values, we processed the autocorrelation values with a moving average window. A cross-correlation vector can be formed by taking the correlation between the output of the matched filter and the scrambling data of the pilot symbol 1 + j. We can then calculate the tap weights by solving the WienerHopf equation. The autocorrelation matrix and crosscorrelation vector are given by (3) and (4) [CITATION_1] , where",
